## Proposed Changes

We will organize the editor into its own dedicated folder `components/editor` to keep things clean.

### 1. Dependencies

We will install the necessary Tiptap extensions and a few helper libraries:
- `@tiptap/extension-task-list` & `@tiptap/extension-task-item`
- `@tiptap/extension-table` (and rows/cells)
- `@tiptap/extension-image` & `@tiptap/extension-youtube`
- `@tiptap/suggestion` & `tippy.js` (for the Slash Commands menu)
- `lucide-react` (for clean, standard editor icons)

### 2. Folder Structure

```text
components/editor/
├── index.tsx              (The main Editor component wrapper)
├── extensions.ts          (Centralized list of all Tiptap capabilities)
├── slash-command.tsx      (The UI popup that appears when you type '/')
├── bubble-menu.tsx        (The floating toolbar for Bold/Italic/Link)
└── default-content.ts     (Helper for empty states)
```
*Note on Server Components:* Tiptap relies heavily on the DOM, so the Editor itself must be a Client Component (`"use client"`). However, the page rendering the editor (e.g. `DocumentPage`) will remain a Server Component, fetching the data and passing it to the Editor as `initialContent` for maximum performance.

### 3. Features to Implement

- **Slash Commands**: Typing `/` will open a dropdown menu (using `tippy.js`) allowing you to insert Headings, Lists, Quotes, etc.
- **Drag Blocks**: We will leverage Tiptap's built-in block drag utilities or a global drag handle to allow reordering.
- **Auto Save & Optimistic Updates**: We will upgrade the existing 1-second debounce to be perfectly seamless, showing a "Saving..." -> "Saved" indicator that instantly reflects local changes while persisting to the server in the background.
- **Blocks**: Headings, Paragraphs, Bullet/Numbered/Task Lists, Code Blocks, Quotes, Dividers.
- **Media**: Image and Video blocks (URL based for now).

